and then i had to do this :

This isn't a PaddleOCR problem. It's a Windows path length limit problem.

You're using Python 3.13 from the Microsoft Store, and PaddleOCR pulls in modelscope, which creates extremely long folder names.

Quick Fix 1 (Recommended)

Enable Windows Long Paths.

Open PowerShell as Administrator and run:

New-ItemProperty -Path "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\FileSystem" `
-Name "LongPathsEnabled" -Value 1 -PropertyType DWORD -Force

Then restart Windows.

After restarting:

pip install paddleocr


